http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Gambling-accused-dies-after-falling-off-police-vehicle/article14021271.ece

A notorious gambler, Badugu Ramudu (40), who was caught by Bandar Taluq police during a raid died after he reportedly fell off the police vehicle on Monday. He was being shifted to police stationRamudu, a native of Gurrala Dibba on the outskirts of Machilipatnam, was said to be in an inebriated condition when the incident occurred. Krishna Superintendent of Police G. Vijay Kumar said that Bandar Taluq SI Mahesh picked up Ramudu and his brother Yesu Babu, for allegedly playing cards and creating nuisance in the village after consuming liquor.While the brothers were being shifted to the police station in a jeep, Ramudu who was in the backseat accidentally fell off the vehicle and suffered a head injury. He was rushed to hospital where he was declared brought dead, the SP said.“Ramudu and his brother were taken into custody for counselling. When the driver applied sudden brake to save a buffalo, the victim fell off the vehicle,” Machilipatnam DSP D. Surya Sravan Kumar said, adding that Ramudu was taken into custody at around 10 a.m. and the incident occurred even before they were shifted to police station.Case registeredA case has been registered and investigation was on. The body was shifted to Government Hospital mortuary for post-mortem.